<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1089,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">
Type data: It is not clear how many females 
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[643,837,1089,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
used to describe this species. One of those specimens bearing original Lepeletier’s label was found at 
<collectionCode box="[688,768,1125,1151]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">MNHP</collectionCode>
and it was interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[1060,1230,1125,1152]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref10360" refString="Moure, J. S. (1960 b) Notas sobre os tipos de abelhas do Brasil descritas por Perty em 1833 (Hymenoptera-Apoidea). Boletim da Universidade Federal do Parana, Zoologia, 1, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
as the “type”. According to the Article 74.6 of the 
<collectionCode box="[519,584,1161,1187]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">ICZN</collectionCode>
(1999) this can be treated as a valid 
<typeStatus box="[988,1091,1161,1187]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. The exemplar has the following data label: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[436,531,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysitis">
<emphasis box="[436,531,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">chrysitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]\ 23 [handwritten]\ [circular label] du nord de la 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1308,1315,1196,1210]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Capite</superScript>
de 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1374,1379,1196,1210]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">St</superScript>
Paul [handwritten]\ Type Lepelletier [handwritten]\ [red label] 
<typeStatus box="[794,898,1233,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Holotype</typeStatus>
[handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty" box="[1071,1319,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maerens">
<emphasis box="[1071,1254,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Centris maerens</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[1326,1347,1233,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
m. type vergl! [handwritten] det. Friese 1898 [printed]\ 
<collectionCode box="[684,772,1269,1295]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">MNHN</collectionCode>
, Paris EY25580 [data matrix code] [printed] (
<collectionCode box="[1287,1374,1269,1295]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">MNHP</collectionCode>
). The type specimen is in good condition.
</paragraph>
